## First order of business : Importing Pico and Flexbox-Grid

I made the initial mistake of not looking for scss specific instructions for this - 
the documentation says to simply do 
<CodeSnippet filename="src/Layouts/Layout.astro">
	```scss
		...
		@use "pico"
	```
</CodeSnippet>

Yeah its not that simple, but after lots of tinkering I've landed at the following
<CodeSnippet filename="src/Layouts/Layout.astro">
``` scss
	...
	@use "flexboxgrid-sass/flexboxgrid";
	@use "@picocss/pico/scss/pico" with 
	(
		$theme-color: "violet", 
		$parent-selector:".pico",
		$breakpoints: (
			sm: (root-font-size: 85%),
			md: (root-font-size: 90%,),
			lg: (root-font-size: 95%),
			xl: (root-font-size: 100%,),
			xxl: (root-font-size: 105%,)
  		),
		$modules: (
			"themes/default": false,
			// Layout
			"layout/document": true,
			"layout/landmarks":false,
			"layout/container":true,)
			... //many other modules
		);

```
</CodeSnippet>
The parent selector bit doesn't seem to work, and I didn't like how it made all my text
cartoonishly large so I overrode that in the breakpoints attribute. SCSS already paying off!

Despite the specification of parent selector, which normally makes pico only affect things 
inside of a '.pico' classed container, typography seems to be the exception to that rule, so
overriding some variables there is necessary. 

I've also discovered that astro makes no guarantees about rule ordering for css so variables
need to be overridden with ```!important```, which is kind of annoying.

I decided to leave layout stuff to flexbox-grid wherever possible, but after installing it
sass kept emitting warnings about depreciation of certain aspects of it.  
They have an automigrator though so fixing it up was easy.  

<CodeSnippet filename="bash">
	``` bash
		npm install -g sass-migrator
		sass-migrator module --migrate-deps node_modules/flexboxgrid-sass/flexboxgrid.scss
		sass-migrator division  node_modules/flexboxgrid-sass/flexboxgrid.scss
	```
</CodeSnippet>

